        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 2:55PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 15 miles north of Ashland to 23 miles
northeast of Sheridan, or extending from 20 miles east of Colstrip
to 23 miles northeast of Sheridan, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashland, Clearmont, Birney, Otter, Birney Village, Moorhead,
Sonnette, Leiter, Arvada and Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
